<Rating>2</Rating>< Review>
Do not go here for traditional pizza styles. You have to get their pizza of the day, otherwise you can't get slices or customize anything. Their 'cheese' pizza, doesn't come with tomato sauce even. The options here are pathetic, but apparently if you like the wild flavors and lack of customization, then this place might be for you.<//Review>

Truly delicious pizza. The crust is crisp and just the right thickness, and I'm always surprised by whatever the pizza of the day is. In my top 3 pizza spots in the bay area, hands down.

The fresh sauces they make to go with their daily pizza are also something you shouldn't miss, they're designed to go together.</Review>

<Name>Glen McKnight< /Name><date>1580219530556<//date><rate>5</rate>< Text>
I absolutely love this pizza and concept. I have never had a slice I didn't like, and their hot sauces you put on the pizza are great additions. In every other pizza world I get pepperoni and black olives every time. Here there is one vegetarian pizza each day. When you get a slice you always get like a half slice with it (thus the name sliver) And if that isn't enough, you can get local beers on tap that run under $5.  They also seem to do a lot for charity.< /Text>

<user>103202217290338153417</user><user_name>P. I.</user_name>< date>
1559951440671< /date>
<Rating>5</Rating>< text>
Another pizza shop in the East Bay with Arizmendi DNA, this chain is the brainchild of a former worker at Berkeley cheese board Pizza collective. Newly installed in the Rockridge shopping center, this is sure to be a big hit in the area, since there is no other Pizza like it in the area. Word to the yum yum.
If you want to know what I mean by Arizmendi DNA, think of delicious pizza but with a crust that is so delicious you can eat it alone without toppings, a kind of chewy fragrant sourdough that they could sell  as bread all on its own. Kind of like putting Pizza on top of a high class focaccia.
Add to that the classic cheese board Pizza collective sauces and toppings, and a rather reasonable price, equals big fun for newcomers to this old pizza recipe sold in a new school joint.< /text>

<gmap_id>0x80dd287871250d79:0xc72ae39c9671f64b< /gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
<rate>5<//rate><response>None< /response><user_id>107653005995473075803</user_id><Gmap_id>0x80dd287871250d79:0xc72ae39c9671f64b</Gmap_id>< user_name>
Roncal / Perez<//user_name>
< text>
We're very happy with our experience with Black Bird. After receiving a fire report for one of our buildings from the L.A. Fire Department, one of the issues we needed to address was bringing all of our fire extinguishers up to date. Luis came and was very professional, and kindly and thoroughly
answered all of our questions and concerns. Our extinguishers needed to be replaced with new ones, and it turns out our existing cabinets for them were not at regulation height (too high), and we'd need to outfit them with small hammers. Luis gave us recommendations on better places to relocate our less-visible extinguishers and moved them. He was also mindful of saving us the cost of purchasing new cabinets and said he'd use the existing cabinets, lowering them on the wall to the correct height and outfitting them with a new poly-scored plexiglass cover that could be broken open without a hammer. He also threw in new locks for them all, which was great. He did all of it that same day as the consultation.

There were other issues we needed to address on the fire report, and normally Black Bird could have handled them if our building had been located completely in Culver City; unfortunately, it's located right on the line between Culver City and the City of Los Angeles, falling more under the jurisdiction of L.A. city which requires a Regulation 4 testing certification. But Luis was happy to refer us directly to an affiliate fire protection company that could handle it, which we really appreciated.

Overall, it was very easy to work with Black Bird, and Luis walked us through each issue ticked on the fire report so we'd have a clear understanding of what we needed to do.< /text>

104347000319066247891< /userid>
<rating>5<//rating>< response>
None< /response>
< Review>
I've loved the Kinokuniya bookstore in Little Tokyo for years. This was my first foray to this one and I love it just as much. FYI: it's located inside the Mitsuwa Marketplace, so when you see that, you're headed in the right direction. I'm a pen junkie, and Kinokuniya has everything I could ever want. I've learned that the Japanese really love their writing implements and are great at developing all types of pens for optimum writing experience. Of course there's manga aplenty, along with tons of awesome blank books, journals, stationery, plushies, cute tote bags (check out the Gojira/Godzilla one). The sales staff are really friendly too. Definitely worth a second and third trip. Plus, right next door is a market specializing in all Japanese food and sundry items, including fresh sushi to go, as well as shops with all manner of Japanese fast food. Shop then eat. Sounds like a plan.</Review>
</record></dataset><record>

<Review>I don't normally give 5 stars, because even if a place is good I always feel there is room for improvement.  Nova Kitchen did not disappoint. <review>Stopped in for dinner on a Saturday night. The first thing I noticed is there was plenty of parking adjacent to the restaurant. The restaurant itself was nicely decorated with an updated modern artistic decor. It creates a nice atmosphere to dine. Abby was our host and she set us up at a nice table facing the bar she was very pleasant,  friendly and professional. Laura our waiter was kind and took great care of us she made us feel welcomed. The food was excellent. We enjoyed everything we tried.

Shishito peppers (not spicy at all, need a little kick & less salt) shrimp tempura (wasn't the traditional tempura, but still good). Brussel sprouts fried rice (really good, recommended. I didn't get to eat much because my boyfriend ate it all). Kung pao chicken, not picture because he already digged in. Not my kind of dish but every man's simple dish is rice and chicken ( not sure why). Korean BBQ rib, small portion wish I had more, I didn't really enjoy much without picking out burtns pieces. It's family style menu yet the decor is so upscale. Prices are a little more than the portion. Overall this was a good experience and we will return. Maybe try a happy hr visit at their beautiful bar. Highly recommend this place. Try it and write your own review they will give you mochi as a compliment, but be honest about. Me and my fiance go out for a date night after we both had our covid vaccine shots.  We pick Nova because they has a very nice outside dining and not just a tent or tables on a sidewalk.  We was surprised that they offered indoor dining room as well.

<text>I went to Nova Kitchen & Bar for takeout during OC Restaurant Week and seeing it featured on Yelp's Top 100 places for 2021! Glad I did and hope to stop by to eat indoors in the post-pandemic era where things are safer.

Something to note that's a wee bit confusing right off the bat - you'll most likely have to park in the hotel parking lot (which is right across from the restaurant). Bring your parking ticket with you as Nova Kitchen will validate even for takeout.

When I got there, it looked super fancy inside (so definitely curious to further explore in the future). I was greeted by a friendly hostess who took my credit card and confirmed my order. Everything was great. The process did take a bit longer than expected since they had to run the card at the bar in the back versus having a credit card reader in the front (and there were issues that night with the machine), but overall, it was a pretty smooth process.

+Pork Belly Bun: Super delicious. Although most of what they did here with their iteration was pretty on par with other pork belly buns, I love that they had some spice to it with the peppers and the presentation even in a to go box was great.
+Miso Cod: The miso cod was also solid. Another really beautiful dish even to go. The sauce is flavorful and love the colors that pop. The fish is cooked solidly here too.
+Strawberry Panna Cotta: Funny enough, the least good looking dish of the group although it tasted great. I imagine this is because they had to separate the panna cotta from the sorbet and thus, the to go solution leaves the panna cotta in its own box and a bit lackluster. However, put them together and the taste is wonderful. Love that the panna cotta isn't overly sweet and that the sorbet has little rock popping candy to give you those childhood memories.<//text><Date>1615658420956</Date>< userid>

<review>This place had me entertained! It‚Äôs a club turned restaurant/event space, and truly I wish it was still a dance club! There is a floor to ceiling TV screen that was oddly playing sports. Really out of place here. The menu was designed eclectically with different element themes matching each of the restaurant‚Äôs rooms -water, earth, fire, air. We joked that maybe we would rotate to the appropriate room corresponding to our next entree!

The food is good, however. It was just such a waste to have such an awesome place be just a restaurant. I had the unagi roll and my coworker had the salmon lemon roll. Both were very good and fresh. Then after that, I was overcharged by $200 on our $500 tab. It took me 1 month of calling the restaurant EVERY SINGLE NIGHT nonstop before the manager even responded to me. They supposedly took down my number a couple times but I never received a call which is why I kept having to call. When the manager finally spoke with me, he said he will file a claim with the company that does their billing and he will CC me in the email that same night. <rate>5< /rate>< Review>
My husband and I had previously used American Vision Windows to install two front windows and an upstairs bedroom window last year.  We were so happy with the experience we decided to get the rest of the windows in the house done as well as the three sliding glass doors.  Since we were going to have all the openings in the house covered, we also decided it would be the time to replace the huge old entry door and sidelights we had with a nice new double door with windows.

We called up Peter, who had sold us the last set of windows, and he came out a few times to walk us through all of our options for the sliders and to make sure the new windows would be the same as the ones we previously had AVW install.  Same as before, Peter was awesome and extremely helpful in working with our budget.

When it came time for measuring, the AVW representative that came to the house was super helpful and even made a special note to our kitchen window as the existing window was going to pose a challenge to retrofit.  We were a little nervous when this was pointed out to us, but he told us that they can handle just about anything and they would make the finished product look right.

Fast forwarding a few months, we got the call for the install and were super happy.  Jason had called us to schedule and then followed up with us two days prior to make sure everything was good to go and if we had any questions.

When install day came, we were told the crew would be at our house between 8:30 am and 9:30 am.  8:00 am on the dot we have the two crews, one for the windows and one for the door, show up and they were ready to go!  They introduced themselves and walked my husband through the order while the rest of the team started setting up.

No joke, the windows and sliders were demoed in about an hour!  They worked super fast and clean, which was nice since it was going to be enough of a challenge putting back the furniture and window treatments later.  Everyone on the window install team was super nice: Jesse, Miguel, Juan, and Steve were very friendly and did a great job.  It was interesting how fast the windows went in and then how much time and care was taken to insulate the gaps, install the molding, and get the windows in show room condition.  The windows and sliders were amazing!  We couldn't believe this was our house!  The window crew was done about 2:30 pm, which was hard to believe that they were able to knock everything out in that amount of time.  The final walkthrough was such a treat, with the challenging kitchen window turning out perfect with a great stucco patch to fix the unsightly gap in the old window.  Total pros!!

The door crew also did an amazing job and wow, that door really made a difference.  Henry and Carlos were great, making the needed adjustments to the opening to get the door in there just right.  Being a double door, we were very sensitive to how the door lined up and how the hardware worked.  When we tried out the door with Henry, everything was nice and snug with the hardware working absolutely perfect.  No more misaligned deadbolt where we had to wiggle the door to get it to set.  No more old heavy wood door!  This was amazing.  Henry was even nice enough to stay behind and quickly re-key the hardware to our existing keys so we could save a trip back to Home Depot to make new keys.  Henry even installed our smart deadbolt and made it look easy.  Everything is working flawlessly!

This was another great experience with American Vision Windows.  We couldn't be happier with everyone we encountered along the way.  The windows, sliders, and entry door have done an amazing job in transforming the look of our house!  We are looking forward to actually being able to open our windows to enjoy the breeze, having sliders that actually slide (imagine that!), and an entry door that is a welcoming focal point to our house.  I can't thank the team enough!!  GREAT JOB!!

- GinGi and Casey Lynch<//Review>

< text>
This review is for RFQ and Window measurement portions. Will update later with actual window installation job.

We were assigned Josh for our window / sliding & french door RFQ. He was able to accommodate our time in the evening to meet with us. He was able to provide succinct answers to our questions. For the most part, nothing was confusing, and if it was, again, we were able to get our answer. After a few weeks we were able to select American Vision out of four other bids to work on our project. Once again, Josh was able to accommodate our busy schedule and meet us in the evening to complete the paperwork. He also came with booties and a mask.

For the measurement portion, Albert came out about a week or so later to get final measurements. He also came with booties and a mask. He answered some questions relating to the outside trim and how it would work installing the frame on the outside. What would be covered up, etc. He finished up the measurement and filled me in on final details. Now we're set for the window installation.

The only bad thing I can say is that the lead-time for the actual windows is way out there since everyone seems to be installing new windows these days (what we heard from American and the other contractors). We'll just have to be patient.

***4/26/21 Update***: Just wanted to give a shout out to American Vision Windows for taking care of us. Windows were installed and look great. We did run into some issues with the roof and window type - but we were very satisfied with how Mike handled the situation. If we have any window projects in the future, we'd definitely give AVW a look again.< /text>

Before I met Craig with his Anlin door system. I had been unhappy with the sliding door installed by the builder on my place for quite sometime but wasn't sure if I was ready to invest in an upgrade. Then I called American Vision for an estimate to see what my options were. They sent out a gentleman named Craig who ran me through my options. His level of customer service and product knowledge made me feel at ease with my decision to upgrade. He took me through the benefits and features of upgrading my sliding glass door and was patient with all my detail oriented questions. I wanted to be sure I was making the right decision and I'm sure glad I did! I can't say enough great things about American Vision. The installation crew was beyond amazing and friendly. <Text>Wow what a company! Long story short. About 18 years ago we had all of  our windows replaced by AVW during our remodel. They explain that the framing sealer was the best out there. That it would last many years. Well 18 years later I noticed a bit of shrinkage around the edges of out front windows to the point where there was a gap where I thought  water may enter during a rain. I called them and in a few days 5 guys showed up, 2 trucks and they proceeded to scrape out old chalking and replace with updated better material. I have 32 windows . They were finished by about 1P.m. Amazing product support and customer service. I have  had zero problems with my windows. They still work and look like new. Every company should take a lesson from these guys. Highly recommended.
These guys have it figured out!

<Text>The staff of American Vision Windows gets 5 stars.  Craig, the representative met with us in our condo and went over the options in a professional, timely and efficient manner.    We chose the Anlin Del-Mar and Malibu Series Windows and Doors.

The remeasure for production of the windows was completed on schedule and the windows arrived ahead of schedule with the installation scheduled at our convenience.

The installation date and start time was reconfirmed several days before the actual install and the installers, Henry, Juan and Enrique arrived on time and did a great job.  They were considerate and did an excellent job on the removal of the old windows and doors, installation of the new windows and cleanup.  The installation took the exact time estimated and was an efficient operation.

We live on a busy street and the windows and doors have eliminated nearly all the outside noise.  I was skeptical such quietness could be achieved.  I'm a believer now.

Definitely would (and have) recommended American Vision to our Neighbors.

<pics>None</pics>< Review>
We had a leak in our windows that American Vision installed a few years ago, so we called to get it fixed.  Albert and Larry showed up (actually a little early which was great) to do the work.  Albert sprayed the window seals on the retrofit windows and no leak appeared.  Then he sprayed from above the original frame and within 20 seconds, it was coming into the house.  Since it was our frame and not the installed windows within the frame, it was actually our problem.

But both men spent a good amount of time repairing the water damage inside, caulking everything, including above the frames of all three windows outside even though only one was leaking. Then Albert explained to me how the frames should have had flashing above them to prevent this issue to begin with. But he said hopefully what they did will fix it.

They went above and beyond even though this was not the fault of the installed windows.  Great service!<//Review>

< time>
1544668132885<//time>
<Rate>5</Rate>< review>
I talked with several different companies before settling on one company.  I didn't want to go to all the effort and expense to install mediocre windows that might prematurely fail to perform the way I wanted.  Also, I wanted American made windows installed by actual employees that are trained by the company, not subcontractors.  American Vision Windows easily met all my needs, and their Anlin Del Mar series seemed perfect!

Our salesman, Robert, did a great job helping us select the perfect set of windows for our needs.  Robert was able to generate fast quotes and last-minute changes with sleight of hand, which was super helpful considering my wife's indecisiveness.  Eventually, we pulled the trigger on a last-minute bay window with Queen Anne engraving.  Robert was able to reassure us both throughout an otherwise expensive, confusing process.

Probably one of the more important issues that came up was the city's fire egress requirements.  Turns out that windows must have a minimum size and area that allow for firemen to enter each bedroom in the event of a fire.  My house is old enough that the original windows were no longer up to the current building code.  All the other companies that I met with had missed that requirement and quoted me for windows that would never pass a building inspection!  Upon entering my bedrooms, however, Robert immediately noticed that my windows would have to be enlarged.  Sure, that meant I had to pay more money, but Robert's knowledge and obvious honesty made me want to rely on American Vision Windows for the whole job!

There is a certain amount of time that must pass between signing a contract for new windows and the actual day of installation--the windows are made according to measurements taken on the house.  But I was not left in a lurch during this time!  American Vision Windows periodically sent out emails informing me about the current state of my windows, what to expect next, information about how my windows were being crafted, as well as information about the company from Bill & Kathleen.  Once my new windows were finished being crafted, Andy and Ryan called me up and schedule a day and time for the installation.  Andy was also super helpful and worked closely with me during scheduling my building inspection with the city.

On installation day, three trucks arrived at 8:00AM full of workers ready to get started installing my new windows.  Within minutes, Pascual, Miguel, Carlos, Aaron, Henry, and Brian were working in every room of my house, removing my old windows and installing the new windows.  As I mentioned above, a couple of my windows had to be enlarged to meet the city's building codes.  These guys were great--with machine-like precision, they demoed my old windows, prepared my rough-in window openings, cut into the stucco where necessary, reinforced my house's frame, and installed the new windows and the bay window by, like, 3:00PM.  The enlarged windows and the bay window would require some stucco patch work, but on the inside, everything was painted with primer and ready for fresh paint.  Even without paint, though, everything looked so much better than before!

On stucco patch day, Albert and Joe arrived promptly at 8:00AM and had everything patched and stuccoed by 12:00PM or so!  These guys are super skilled in cement work--they even modded some brickwork near my kitchen windows so they'd match all the other windows.  Albert and Joe happily worked with me and answered all my questions about cement, stucco, primer, and paint.  And, their stucco work looks better than I had imagined, I can't wait to paint it!

I am grateful to all of these guys for their solid skills and great work, and I am super glad I went with American Vision Windows.  Too bad I can't hire them to renovate my back yard, lol.  So, I wholeheartedly recommend American Vision Windows for all you window needs!<//review>

The salesman gave me a date about 5 weeks later to check status with the office.The "production measurement" guy was an hour late but completed his task quickly and thoroughly when he arrived, taking pictures so the install team knew what to expect. Due to the age of the house I needed a noninvasive lead paint inspection which went smoothly. The day before I was to call for status AVW called to schedule installation. The installation team arrived on time. Installation went extremely well, the performance was almost like a well choreographed dance. Drop cloths and plastic was used to protect floor and furniture. Cleanup was complete, even including some minor paint touchup. Installation was complete a few minutes earlier than the estimate given when I made the appointment.< /Review>

<pictures>None<//pictures>< Review>
At first we were skeptical. How could a company live up to the promise of a virtually painless experience?  When the salesman came to our home he was extremely knowledgeable, answered all of our questions, showed us examples for the various window components, and demonstrated what the company was about.  But this was the only demo!  We really wanted new windows.  The old casement crank-style windows were a real pain.  The leaked air in winter and summer, driving our heating and cooling costs through the roof.  We placed our order and held our breath.

Although we had a few scheduling problems, one Friday morning at 9:30am the crew from American Vision Windows arrived.  Here was the truckload with our eight custom built windows, and all the crew needed, ready to start the install.  It was amazing to watch how they worked so well as a team.  Each performed their overlapping tasks of window removal, trim to perfect fit, install, insulating, and final trim with efficient expertise.  I had worried about how they were going to get the old windows out without tearing up the stucco.  How could they possibly do this in a day?  My fears went away when i saw how they skillfully removed the old windows, preserving the integrity of the existing frame.  The stucco was untouched, and the new Anlin double pane, argon-filled windows slid right in.  Our leaky, falling-apart garden window was gone in minutes, replaced by a beautiful kitchen window that was a perfect fit.

By 2:30 pm, eight windows on all sides of our house were installed.  We were amazed at the difference in the appearance of the house, both inside and out.  When they were done, the crew cleaned up and hauled away all the old windows and glass.

I would recommend American Vision Windows to anyone for three reasons.  1) The quality product they sell, 2) the job that the crew performed, and 3) Value I received for the money.  My only regret is that I didn't have this done four years ago when I first moved into the house.< /Review>
